01/10/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Bosnian Serb law enforcement authorities have launched a "low profile" operation to find and arrest war crimes suspects, AFP reported Thursday (30 September). 
The wire service was quoting a source in the Republika Srpska (RS) police. 
An SFOR spokesman welcomed the apparent move, reiterating the peacekeeper's commitment to help.
In other news, SFOR says the Bosnian Serb Army has started to destroy its surplus heavy weapons. 
An estimated 1,000 pieces of equipment, including tanks, armoured personnel carriers, mortars, artillery, rocket-propelled grenades and rocket launching systems are to be scrapped. 
(AFP - 29/09/04)
